thread.title: Latham suspension lifted immediately
thread.title_full: Latham suspension lifted immediately | Indiana Daily Student

author: IDS Reports
title: Latham suspension lifted immediately
text:
Junior defensive lineman Darius Latham's suspension has been lifted, IU Athletics announced Friday afternoon.
Latham will participate in IU's week six match-up with Penn State, as the suspension is lifted immediately.
Latham was suspended indefinitely by IU last week until proceedings with the Office of Student Ethics were completed.
He was also one of nine players to be suspended for the first week of the season versus Southern Illinois for undisclosed reasons.
In three games this season, the defensive lineman has recorded 10 tackles, five tackles for loss and two sacks.
Taylor Lehman
